Encapsulation bundles data with methods and restricts direct access. Make fields private, provide public getters/setters. Protects data integrity. Example: private int age; public int getAge() { return age; } public void setAge(int age) { if(age > 0) this.age = age; }. Core OOP principle for maintainable code.